data.description: Quaint home in downtown Jacksonville. Just a short walk to Sturgeon City Park and Wilson Bay. If you want a home to make custom updates and make your own, look no further. This home has a full-sized basement that is partially heated and unfinished for full customization. The main living areas have original hardwood floors and a formal dining room. The fireplace has been converted to gas logs. The large back deck leading off the dining room overlooks your own personal oasis in the backyard. Not only does the home have city water access, but it also has a well and well pump. This home truly is a diamond in the rough. *Home is being sold as is* The pool, pool deck, and blue shed do not covey. *All room measurements are estimates; the buyer to verify all measurements and square footage***
